Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.60,0:00:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,be a lot more simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.56,0:00:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There was only one phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.98,0:00:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We now have three different
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.40,0:00:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,screen sizes for iPhone and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.04,0:00:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,three iPad sizes, with different
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.83,0:00:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,orientations, and split screens,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.81,0:00:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and multitasking screens.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.35,0:00:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And that might seem like a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.20,0:00:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of different screen sizes to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.33,0:00:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,consider, but there's a basic
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.13,0:00:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,framework for designing and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.75,0:00:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,building your app that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.03,0:00:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,simplifies the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.13,0:00:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This will save you time and your
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.66,0:00:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,app will look great regardless
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.73,0:00:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of what device people are using.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.82,0:00:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The key things to consider are
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.83,0:01:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,organizing your screens into
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.90,0:01:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,size classes, using Dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.34,0:01:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Type, and taking advantage of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.13,0:01:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,standard UI elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.16,0:01:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of these things are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.79,0:01:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,meant to make it easier for you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.96,0:01:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to design and build your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.45,0:01:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, first let's take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.09,0:01:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,size classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.88,0:01:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All screen sizes -- all iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.63,0:01:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,screen dimensions fall under one
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.84,0:01:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of two size classes, compact or
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.52,0:01:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,regular.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.91,0:01:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And an easy way to think about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.28,0:01:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,this is that the narrower screen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.79,0:01:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,widths are compact size, like an
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.12,0:01:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.41,0:01:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And a wider screen widths are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.12,0:01:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,regular like the width of an
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.97,0:01:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,iPad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.28,0:01:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stack all of the screens
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.87,0:01:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,on top of each other, in both
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.99,0:01:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,portrait and in landscape
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.45,0:01:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,orientations you can see that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.42,0:01:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,size class applies to both width
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.44,0:01:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and height.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.94,0:01:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The goal of creating these two
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.45,0:01:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,size classes is so that layouts
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.76,0:01:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,will be flexible and elements
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.46,0:01:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,will adapt relative to their
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.01,0:01:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,screen size.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.26,0:01:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So let me give you a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.26,0:02:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,examples of what that might
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.20,0:02:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,potentially mean for your
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.38,0:02:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.26,0:02:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The iPhone 7 Plus in landscape,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.16,0:02:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,falls under regular width, which
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.97,0:02:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,allows it to use Split Views
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.75,0:02:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,like all of the iPads.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.78,0:02:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the two smaller phones in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.94,0:02:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape are compact in both
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.10,0:02:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,width and height.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.95,0:02:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This means they will get shorter
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.79,0:02:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape bar heights than the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.23,0:02:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,standard height that you see in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.55,0:02:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,portrait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.07,0:02:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Screen widths also define UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.87,0:02:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,margins and margin, the margin
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.62,0:02:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,widths can either be standard or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.99,0:02:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,like this iPad generous for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.10,0:02:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,wider screens.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.07,0:02:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But in this example and a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.75,0:02:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,other cases, text, if text went
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.04,0:02:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,edge to edge with the UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.59,0:02:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,margins then the lines of text
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.52,0:02:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,would be too long making it hard
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.63,0:02:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for the eye to jump down when
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.14,0:02:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to the end of a line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.93,0:02:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we use readability margins
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.85,0:02:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to restrict the line lengths on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.35,0:02:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,larger devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.07,0:03:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,These margins are flexible
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.55,0:03:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because they can vary with the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.78,0:03:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.75,0:03:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And smaller text needs more
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.29,0:03:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,narrow readability lengths, and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.62,0:03:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,larger text can have longer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.12,0:03:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,lengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.47,0:03:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're using Dynamic Type
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.31,0:03:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,with readability margins, then
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.99,0:03:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,people using your app will have
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.23,0:03:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a much more comfortable reading
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.64,0:03:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.81,0:03:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's talk more about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.02,0:03:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type, what it is and how
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.68,0:03:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it can help people use your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.05,0:03:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type are predefined text
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.29,0:03:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,styles that can be scaled on a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.79,0:03:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,device so that people can see
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.83,0:03:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,text at a size that is most
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.32,0:03:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,comfortable for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.21,0:03:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are a lot of people
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.18,0:03:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,who find text in their apps to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.42,0:03:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,be way too small to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.44,0:03:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, using Dynamic Type will
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.81,0:03:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically allow text to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.66,0:03:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,scale up or down without
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.57,0:03:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,compromising your layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.75,0:03:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And it also makes opting in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.65,0:03:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Settings for even
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.45,0:03:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,larger type, much easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.12,0:03:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It also makes localizing your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.59,0:04:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,app seamless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.80,0:04:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Your text will adjust the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,lettering, or line height based
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.83,0:04:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,on the height of the characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.47,0:04:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So using these features will
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.84,0:04:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,only make it easier for more
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.10,0:04:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,people to use your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.55,0:04:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is our Dynamic Type
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.96,0:04:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.03,0:04:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And this year, we've made some
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.37,0:04:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,adjustments to our existing text
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.09,0:04:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,styles by increasing the weight
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.99,0:04:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of Title sizes from light to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.16,0:04:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,regular.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.43,0:04:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In most cases, we recommend
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.59,0:04:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,using two to three of these text
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.88,0:04:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,styles per screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.03,0:04:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But with ten different text
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.31,0:04:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,styles to choose from, there are
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.32,0:04:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,countless combinations and a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.81,0:04:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of flexibility when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.49,0:04:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,designing your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.28,0:04:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The names of the text styles are
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.69,0:04:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,meant to be descriptive,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.35,0:04:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,suggesting where certain styles
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.64,0:04:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are most appropriately used.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.00,0:04:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So for instance, Body is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.93,0:04:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,intended to be used in places
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.99,0:04:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,where large bodies of text are
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.58,0:04:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.42,0:04:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And Body is also the default
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.72,0:04:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that we use throughout the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.88,0:04:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,system.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.60,0:04:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And from there, we can introduce
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.49,0:05:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,smaller and larger styles, or in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.78,0:05:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,this case bolder, to create
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.37,0:05:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.57,0:05:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if you're using a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,custom font in your design?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.14,0:05:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this year, with our new API
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.88,0:05:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we have, we can make custom
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.54,0:05:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,fonts Dynamic as well, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.22,0:05:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,great.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.11,0:05:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind that you may have
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.58,0:05:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to design -- assign different
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.45,0:05:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,point sizes for each text style
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.68,0:05:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because not all fonts have the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.27,0:05:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,same proportions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.11,0:05:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is important for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.40,0:05:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping your text optically the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.89,0:05:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,same size.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.35,0:05:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Etsy is a good example of an app
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.25,0:05:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that uses Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.00,0:05:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is at its default size,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.00,0:05:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and here it is at a much larger
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.69,0:05:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,size, and it looks great.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.78,0:05:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, last but not least, let's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.95,0:05:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,discuss UIKit Elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.22,0:05:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than focusing effort on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.11,0:05:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,designing a task or function
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that people are already familiar
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.53,0:05:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with, we want you to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.30,0:05:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,focus your time designing what
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.97,0:05:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,makes your app unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.29,0:05:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a bunch of standard UI
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.73,0:06:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,elements that you can use in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.08,0:06:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your app that will automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.82,0:06:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,adapt on all screen sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.21,0:06:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this includes things like
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.31,0:06:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,TableViews which not only scale
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.24,0:06:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,nicely with Dynamic Type, it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.22,0:06:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,also inherits readability
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.56,0:06:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,margins and standard
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.86,0:06:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,interactions, like swipe
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.29,0:06:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,actions, and edit mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.14,0:06:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are a lot of other
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.12,0:06:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,resources that will help enforce
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.31,0:06:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,consistency and adapt seamlessly
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.54,0:06:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,across devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.81,0:06:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to note that all
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.53,0:06:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of these components are scaled
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.12,0:06:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for iOS 7, which is the size
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.27,0:06:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that we recommend you start a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.67,0:06:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,new design.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.79,0:06:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you have an iPhone design
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.84,0:06:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a couple tips for
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.02,0:06:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,adapting it to iPad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.07,0:06:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, going back for a minute, we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.91,0:06:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,now know that regular size
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.69,0:06:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,classes or iPads can use Split
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.26,0:06:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Views and to maintain content
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.74,0:06:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,hierarchy between iPhone and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.60,0:06:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,iPad consider how your app will
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.70,0:06:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,relay out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.87,0:06:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The left side of the Split View
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.33,0:06:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,can be referred to as the Master
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.27,0:06:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,View.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.67,0:07:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the right is the Detail
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.24,0:07:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,View.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.42,0:07:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Detail View on an iPhone
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.88,0:07:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the page you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.92,0:07:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,drill down further to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.21,0:07:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, an iPad will share
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.72,0:07:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,both iPad and iPhone specific
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.84,0:07:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,layouts and iPad layouts should
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.33,0:07:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,maintain the same level of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.60,0:07:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,hierarchy as the iPhone layout
